Title: CHIRAL SYMMETRIES OF THE WZNW MODEL BY HAMILTONIAN METHODS

Authors: B. Sazdovi\'c

Comments: 8 pages, Plain Tex

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B352 (1995) 64-68

The connection between the Kac-Moody algebras of currents and the chiralsymmetries of the two dimensional WZNW model is clarified. It is shown thatonly the zero modes of the Kac-Moody currents are the first class constraints,and that, consequently, the corresponding gauge symmetries are chiral.